Blue is blue IS CORRECT.......
To explain, 'Blue' can be used as both a noun and an adjective, ie. you can describe something as blue(which is the adjective use) or identify the colour of blue(which is the noun use). Therefore the colour Blue(ie. the noun), can be described as blue. Therefore AJ was correct.
You can think of describing 'Water as watery'. Here it is easier to see why it works because the adjective is different to the noun. However, it is the same principle because water is only water, because it is 'watery'.
